text: Cockburn Island is an island in the Canadian province of Ontario, found in the Manitoulin District. It has the least number of people living in it while still being a municipality of Canada. Its population was counted as 16 people in 2021. However, more people live on the island during the summer. There was an Indian reservation, or place where Indians live, on Cockburn Island.
